href="erct-004B.xml"
addr="erct-004B"
title="Reflexive graph">reflexive graph</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {A}]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em><fr:strong>univalent</fr:strong></fr:em> when for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x:  \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {} ]]></fr:tex> the type <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen y:  \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {} \right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen y:  \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {} \right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen y:  \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {} \right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen y:  \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {} \right \rparen \mathclose {} }} x\approx _{\mathcal {A}} y]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>, or (equivalently), is <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001H.xml"
addr="erct-001H"
title="Contractible type">contractible</fr:link> with centre <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {rx}_{\mathcal {A}}{x}\right \rparen \mathclose {} ]]></fr:tex>. We shall refer to a univalent <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-004B.xml"
addr="erct-004B"
title="Reflexive graph">reflexive graph</fr:link> as a <fr:em><fr:strong>path object</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p><fr:p>We will write <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {PathObj}]]></fr:tex> for the (large) type of path objects. In our notation, we will at times silently coerce a given path object to its underlying type of vertices.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
